  "The constant velocity reached when air resistance equals the force of gravity": "",
  "The maximum velocity an object can have before it breaks apart due to stress": "",
  "The velocity at which a projectile hits the ground at the end of its fall": "",
  "The initial velocity needed to launch a projectile to its maximum range": "",
  "Terminal velocity occurs when air resistance equals gravity, so net force is zero and the object stops accelerating. It falls at a constant speed. This is not true free fall since air resistance is present.": "",
